1
00:00:58,106 --> 00:01:00,026
My name is Petchgam Ploy.

2
00:01:00,026 --> 00:01:02,026
I am here as the Purser.

3
00:01:02,026 --> 00:01:03,226
Wait...THE PURSER?!

4
00:01:03,226 --> 00:01:06,146
Every time I see you, an evaluation is happening.

5
00:01:06,146 --> 00:01:09,266
Because from now on, every step you take will be scored,
including your looks.

6
00:01:09,266 --> 00:01:11,706
Whoever gets the highest score becomes "The First Class."

7
00:01:11,706 --> 00:01:13,346
So that means those who don't make the cut...

8
00:01:13,346 --> 00:01:15,186
Say goodbye to Glamorous Airline.

9
00:01:15,186 --> 00:01:17,706
Doctor Yep is a massive social media sensation!

10
00:01:17,706 --> 00:01:19,386
If he does our faces...

11
00:01:19,386 --> 00:01:21,946
We’re definitely getting promoted to First Class.

12
00:01:21,946 --> 00:01:23,026
That will be 480,000 baht.

13
00:01:23,026 --> 00:01:23,546
We leave!

14
00:01:23,546 --> 00:01:26,426
No, I’m going out First Class pretty only.

15
00:01:27,306 --> 00:01:32,346
Welcome to Glamorous Airline.

16
00:01:32,346 --> 00:01:36,306
You probably think this is a safety demonstration video, right?

17
00:01:36,306 --> 00:01:40,066
Wrong. Because this video has zero substance.

18
00:01:40,066 --> 00:01:41,786
We’re just here to flex the luxury...

19
00:01:41,786 --> 00:01:45,266
of our brand-new aircraft and our brand-new class.

20
00:01:45,266 --> 00:01:47,586
First Class.

21
00:01:47,586 --> 00:01:50,466
Where you can sin without a worry...

22
00:01:50,466 --> 00:01:53,466
because we’ve literally brought heaven down to your seat.

23
00:01:55,386 --> 00:01:59,586
A cabin designed to be minimalist yet expensive.

24
00:01:59,586 --> 00:02:02,946
Because every single angle was intended to look "Rich."

25
00:02:02,946 --> 00:02:05,866
What you see here aren't lights.

26
00:02:05,866 --> 00:02:09,626
It’s the aura radiating from you once you take a seat with us.

27
00:02:09,626 --> 00:02:12,786
Featuring the latest 8K monitors.

28
00:02:12,786 --> 00:02:16,546
Four times sharper than 4K.

29
00:02:16,546 --> 00:02:20,546
Sixteen times sharper than Full HD.

30
00:02:20,706 --> 00:02:24,466
Honestly, it's sharper than the reality of your own life.

31
00:02:24,466 --> 00:02:27,666
In other classes, you adjust to the seat.

32
00:02:27,666 --> 00:02:31,066
But here, the seat adjusts to you.

33
00:02:31,066 --> 00:02:35,546
The recline is deeper than your ex’s moral standards.

34
00:02:38,226 --> 00:02:41,586
Our meals are crafted from the finest ingredients.

35
00:02:41,586 --> 00:02:46,106
The cows are literally confused about how they became this premium.

36
00:02:48,226 --> 00:02:49,226
Is it delicious?

37
00:03:06,066 --> 00:03:07,066
Holy shit!

38
00:03:13,666 --> 00:03:14,666
I can’t take this anymore!

39
00:03:16,626 --> 00:03:19,506
Wait! Where are you going?

40
00:03:19,506 --> 00:03:20,146
Please don't leave yet!

41
00:03:20,146 --> 00:03:21,186
I’m done with this!

42
00:03:21,186 --> 00:03:23,186
Wait, wait, just a second! Where are you going?

43
00:03:25,626 --> 00:03:26,626
What is all this?

44
00:03:26,826 --> 00:03:28,826
Gift, I’ll save you!

45
00:03:35,426 --> 00:03:36,426
What the hell...

46
00:03:37,986 --> 00:03:38,986
How the hell did it get here?

47
00:03:40,906 --> 00:03:41,906
I’m outta here!

48
00:03:42,226 --> 00:03:44,226
Where do you think you’re going? Get back here!

49
00:03:44,866 --> 00:03:45,866
Who pulled my shirt?

50
00:03:47,666 --> 00:03:48,666
Tid-Gift, are you okay?

51
00:03:50,306 --> 00:03:51,306
Oh, Sky! You too?

52
00:03:52,346 --> 00:03:53,346
I thought it was just me.

53
00:03:53,786 --> 00:03:55,786
Say it clearly! It’s my chest!

54
00:03:55,946 --> 00:03:56,946
What?

55
00:03:58,986 --> 00:03:59,986
Stop!

56
00:04:01,786 --> 00:04:02,786
You want a piece of me?

57
00:04:05,986 --> 00:04:06,986
Stop!

58
00:04:07,506 --> 00:04:10,506
Both of you, STOP!

59
00:04:16,946 --> 00:04:19,706
Thank God, it was a dream...a total nightmare.

60
00:04:19,706 --> 00:04:21,706
Yeah, I had a nightmare too.

61
00:04:23,906 --> 00:04:26,426
But Chai...you were low-key packing down there in that dream.

62
00:04:28,466 --> 00:04:30,466
Wait, what? No, that was just a dream!

63
00:04:31,906 --> 00:04:34,866
Wait a minute...did the three of us have the exact same dream?

64
00:04:34,866 --> 00:04:38,866
Maybe our heads were touching while we slept,
so the dreams synced up?

65
00:04:40,786 --> 00:04:43,426
No, I don't think that was a dream.

66
00:04:43,426 --> 00:04:47,426
Well, if it wasn't a dream,
then you’re definitely packing down there.

67
00:04:49,466 --> 00:04:51,466
That part might be a dream...

68
00:04:51,466 --> 00:04:55,466
But the part where we’re flying First Class together...

69
00:05:01,186 --> 00:05:02,706
Is 100% real!

70
00:05:02,706 --> 00:05:04,706
We finally will be promoted!

71
00:05:12,146 --> 00:05:15,746
Mom, they’ve renovated the airport a bit.

72
00:05:15,746 --> 00:05:17,826
It might not look the same; you might not even recognize it.

73
00:05:17,826 --> 00:05:21,826
The new signs say Gate A1 is this way...

74
00:05:21,946 --> 00:05:23,866
and Gate A2 is over that way.

75
00:05:23,866 --> 00:05:26,786
I have no idea why A1 and A2 aren't next to each other.

76
00:05:26,786 --> 00:05:28,106
Classic Glamorous Airline...

77
00:05:28,106 --> 00:05:31,066
I want you to wear a warm coat, Mom.
Take care of yourself.

78
00:05:31,066 --> 00:05:35,066
And tell Siri not to overdo it, she’s still recovering.

79
00:05:35,426 --> 00:05:36,546
Who the hell are you talking to?

80
00:05:36,546 --> 00:05:37,906
All I see is your face in the camera.

81
00:05:37,906 --> 00:05:38,906
I’m recording a video!

82
00:05:40,386 --> 00:05:43,466
My mom is up in the mountains, there’s no signal there.

83
00:05:43,466 --> 00:05:46,306
You’re making a video for your mom?
How do you even know she misses you?

84
00:05:46,306 --> 00:05:50,306
Hey! My mom took Siri for treatment until she's cured, okay?

85
00:05:50,386 --> 00:05:52,026
Siri!

86
00:05:52,026 --> 00:05:55,026
Right now, I just want to take Siri to England for treatment.

87
00:05:57,066 --> 00:06:00,066
After being apart for this long,
what kind of mother wouldn't miss her own kid?

88
00:06:01,066 --> 00:06:03,826
Mom, listen...

89
00:06:03,826 --> 00:06:06,826
Yeah, you're right.
My mom must really miss me too.

90
00:06:14,026 --> 00:06:14,626
Mom?

91
00:06:14,626 --> 00:06:16,186
What is it? I’m playing cards!

92
00:06:16,186 --> 00:06:17,626
Natural Nine!

93
00:06:17,626 --> 00:06:20,626
You little brat! Why are you calling me now?
You ruined my hand!

94
00:06:21,266 --> 00:06:22,266
Oh...

95
00:06:26,786 --> 00:06:27,786
Mom!

96
00:06:28,226 --> 00:06:31,746
How did you know?
This is Mommy Duang from HR.

97
00:06:31,746 --> 00:06:33,746
Mommy Duang from HR?

98
00:06:34,506 --> 00:06:35,506
Huh?

99
00:06:42,506 --> 00:06:43,146
What?

100
00:06:43,146 --> 00:06:44,106
All-New, something happened!

101
00:06:44,106 --> 00:06:45,186
Hold on.

102
00:06:45,186 --> 00:06:46,226
Mom, it's like Glamorous...

103
00:06:46,226 --> 00:06:48,946
Ugh, "Mom" this, "Mom" that. You're obsessed!

104
00:06:48,946 --> 00:06:50,626
Move it, let's go! Something happened!

105
00:06:50,626 --> 00:06:53,826
Gotta go, Mom. I don't know what's wrong with Kreetha, but...

106
00:06:53,826 --> 00:06:54,746
Hey!

107
00:06:54,746 --> 00:06:55,666
Move, move!

108
00:06:55,666 --> 00:06:56,666
Hey, man.

109
00:06:58,066 --> 00:06:59,066
Mom, love you!

110
00:07:02,426 --> 00:07:05,346
By the way, when is Chaba coming back to work?

111
00:07:05,346 --> 00:07:07,186
She’s been on leave for months.

112
00:07:07,186 --> 00:07:07,906
Wait.

113
00:07:07,906 --> 00:07:10,866
Did I seriously not tell you guys about Chaba yet?

114
00:07:10,866 --> 00:07:14,866
What happened to her?

115
00:07:16,586 --> 00:07:17,626
We're all dead.

116
00:07:17,626 --> 00:07:18,306
What?

117
00:07:18,306 --> 00:07:20,226
Huh?

118
00:07:20,226 --> 00:07:21,226
We're all dead!

119
00:07:22,186 --> 00:07:23,186
We're all dead!

120
00:07:23,306 --> 00:07:26,026
Our airline is changing the plan!
We’re only flying First Class now!

121
00:07:26,026 --> 00:07:27,746
Ugh! I thought you meant something happened to Chaba!

122
00:07:27,746 --> 00:07:29,906
Ugh, that is "So Yesterday."

123
00:07:29,906 --> 00:07:33,506
Are you just now realizing we’re being promoted to First Class?

124
00:07:33,506 --> 00:07:35,506
Uh...there’s more bad news.

125
00:07:36,746 --> 00:07:37,746
Which is...

126
00:07:40,186 --> 00:07:40,426
Wait!

127
00:07:40,626 --> 00:07:41,626
Look!

128
00:07:42,866 --> 00:07:43,866
Chaba!

129
00:07:44,066 --> 00:07:45,066
Chaba...

130
00:07:45,586 --> 00:07:47,986
Don’t tell me...Chaba is...

131
00:07:47,986 --> 00:07:48,986
All-New...

132
00:07:49,706 --> 00:07:52,706
Chaba...is it true? Tell me it’s not true!

133
00:07:53,226 --> 00:07:54,506
Gift!

134
00:07:54,506 --> 00:07:57,626
Are you insane? Look at this!

135
00:07:57,626 --> 00:08:01,026
Chaba just Line-ed me.
She’s coming in to pick up her new uniform.

136
00:08:01,026 --> 00:08:03,466
What the hell? She’s not dead!
Nobody’s dead!

137
00:08:03,466 --> 00:08:06,386
Then what is this photo doing here?

138
00:08:06,386 --> 00:08:09,826
Oh, I saw it sitting by the elevator, so I just picked it up.

139
00:08:09,826 --> 00:08:12,586
Chaba probably printed it as a souvenir.

140
00:08:12,586 --> 00:08:14,746
She went away to focus on losing weight.

141
00:08:14,746 --> 00:08:18,586
Whoa...is this new uniform for Chaba?

142
00:08:18,586 --> 00:08:22,586
Holy...how much weight did she actually lose?

143
00:08:29,866 --> 00:08:30,866
Chaba!

144
00:08:35,866 --> 00:08:36,866
Oh my God.

145
00:08:38,666 --> 00:08:44,666
Chaba, are you free for dinner with me tonight?

146
00:08:45,746 --> 00:08:48,026
I’m free, Chai.

147
00:08:48,026 --> 00:08:50,146
Great, because...

148
00:08:50,146 --> 00:08:52,106
Wait, who the hell is that?

149
00:08:52,106 --> 00:08:53,746
Who are you?

150
00:08:53,746 --> 00:08:55,986
You just ripped my photo!

151
00:08:55,986 --> 00:08:59,266
Chaba, did you lose too much weight?
Are you on pills?

152
00:08:59,266 --> 00:09:00,266
No pills.

153
00:09:00,266 --> 00:09:02,586
Just working out, eating greens and fruits.

154
00:09:02,586 --> 00:09:04,466
Drinking only healthy stuff.

155
00:09:04,466 --> 00:09:05,706
Chugging energy boosters.

156
00:09:05,706 --> 00:09:06,706
And sniffing poppers.

157
00:09:10,626 --> 00:09:13,306
Thank God...

158
00:09:13,306 --> 00:09:15,306
that you didn't end up skinny like that girl.

159
00:09:17,186 --> 00:09:20,186
But I actually did lose a lot of weight.

160
00:09:21,626 --> 00:09:23,626
But you’re still not as pretty as her.

161
00:09:26,186 --> 00:09:28,666
Anyway, who are you?

162
00:09:28,666 --> 00:09:29,626
Right.

163
00:09:29,626 --> 00:09:33,626
Since we’re all moving up to First Class...

164
00:09:33,706 --> 00:09:35,546
Someone has to take over Economy, right?

165
00:09:35,546 --> 00:09:37,706
Correct. I’m new here.

166
00:09:37,706 --> 00:09:40,546
But I’m not here to work with you.

167
00:09:40,546 --> 00:09:44,546
Well, then you better pay your respects to your seniors.
What are you waiting for?

168
00:09:44,866 --> 00:09:46,866
I’m waiting to introduce myself.

169
00:09:51,386 --> 00:09:54,866
My name is Petchgam.

170
00:09:54,866 --> 00:09:56,706
Ploy.

171
00:09:56,706 --> 00:10:00,146
Ployglamjetz.

172
00:10:00,146 --> 00:10:01,946
Wait...so is it Petchgam?

173
00:10:01,946 --> 00:10:02,706
Ploy...

174
00:10:02,706 --> 00:10:03,546
And Ploy is...

175
00:10:03,546 --> 00:10:05,026
It's Petchgam Ploy.

176
00:10:05,026 --> 00:10:06,506
Wait, what is your actual name?

177
00:10:06,506 --> 00:10:08,306
Petchgam. Middle name is Ploy.

178
00:10:08,306 --> 00:10:09,946
You should address me by both:

179
00:10:09,946 --> 00:10:11,186
Petchgam Ploy.

180
00:10:11,186 --> 00:10:13,546
Yikes. This newbie is such a diva.

181
00:10:13,546 --> 00:10:14,466
Tell me about it.

182
00:10:14,466 --> 00:10:16,186
No, no, no, no. Don't say that.

183
00:10:16,186 --> 00:10:20,546
I may be new to your faces,
but I'm not working alongside you.

184
00:10:20,546 --> 00:10:22,986
I am here as the Purser.

185
00:10:22,986 --> 00:10:25,666
Phew...just a Purser.

186
00:10:25,666 --> 00:10:27,666
Wait...THE PURSER?!

187
00:10:32,026 --> 00:10:33,826
Oh! Hello, Ma'am!

188
00:10:33,826 --> 00:10:36,866
I’m Sky. I’ve been working here for...
oh, I’m such a hard worker!

189
00:10:36,866 --> 00:10:37,906
What is my name again?

190
00:10:37,906 --> 00:10:39,586
Ms. Petchgam Joy?

191
00:10:39,586 --> 00:10:40,106
Joy what?

192
00:10:40,106 --> 00:10:40,946
Joy-glam-jets!

193
00:10:40,946 --> 00:10:41,666
Yes! I totally remember!

194
00:10:41,666 --> 00:10:42,706
It's Petchgam Ploy.

195
00:10:42,706 --> 00:10:43,346
Yes, Ma'am!

196
00:10:43,346 --> 00:10:44,106
Petchgam Ploy.

197
00:10:44,106 --> 00:10:45,506
Are you okay, Chaba?

198
00:10:45,506 --> 00:10:48,506
No, I’m actually about to faint. I can't take this.

199
00:10:51,666 --> 00:10:53,906
See? No one ever lets me finish.

200
00:10:53,906 --> 00:10:55,626
I was trying to tell you that HR...

201
00:10:55,626 --> 00:10:57,946
asked me to bring this uniform to the new Purser.

202
00:10:57,946 --> 00:10:59,266
The one who’s here to evaluate us.

203
00:10:59,266 --> 00:11:00,266
But no, nobody listened to me!

204
00:11:06,986 --> 00:11:09,786
Mr. Kreetha, thank you for the uniform.

205
00:11:09,786 --> 00:11:13,306
Wait, what did you call me, Ms. Petchgam Ploy?

206
00:11:13,306 --> 00:11:17,146
I said, thank you for the uniform, Mr. Kreetha.

207
00:11:17,146 --> 00:11:19,546
You...you actually know my name?

208
00:11:19,546 --> 00:11:23,346
Of course. I also know that you, Mr. Kreetha...

209
00:11:23,346 --> 00:11:27,026
are a spy who is incredibly smooth and terrifyingly professional.

210
00:11:27,026 --> 00:11:31,026
But in the end, you’re just a cute little puppy.

211
00:11:37,186 --> 00:11:38,146
What are you doing?

212
00:11:38,146 --> 00:11:42,146
I'm memorizing this first impression,
letting it sink into my cerebrum.

213
00:11:42,706 --> 00:11:46,706
As for you, Mr. Chai.

214
00:11:46,866 --> 00:11:50,026
Truly the "Big Brother" to every flight attendant.

215
00:11:50,026 --> 00:11:53,346
You’re always the one looking out for your colleagues...

216
00:11:53,346 --> 00:11:56,506
And every single passenger. To the point where...

217
00:11:56,506 --> 00:11:58,026
it’s too much.

218
00:11:58,026 --> 00:11:59,266
Way too much.

219
00:11:59,266 --> 00:12:01,346
Over the top.

220
00:12:01,346 --> 00:12:05,026
Miss Tid-Gift, you’re small but you’ve got a big mouth.

221
00:12:05,026 --> 00:12:06,786
But your heart?

222
00:12:06,786 --> 00:12:07,346
Soft.

223
00:12:07,346 --> 00:12:08,226
Sensitive.

224
00:12:08,226 --> 00:12:09,346
Fragile.

225
00:12:09,346 --> 00:12:10,586
Easily swayed.

226
00:12:10,586 --> 00:12:12,586
Especially by men.

227
00:12:15,666 --> 00:12:22,186
Mr. All-New, you’re the adopted child / secret spy for Madam Porn.

228
00:12:22,186 --> 00:12:25,466
And you’re a bookworm.

229
00:12:25,466 --> 00:12:27,466
Also...a worm in the system. A mole.

230
00:12:28,706 --> 00:12:32,146
Miss Chaba, our "plus-size" flight attendant.

231
00:12:32,146 --> 00:12:35,906
You have such persistence and determination to lose weight.

232
00:12:35,906 --> 00:12:39,906
Sometimes it makes you look a bit...blurry, dazed, and confused.

233
00:12:40,626 --> 00:12:43,066
But I guess it's somewhat "cute."

234
00:12:43,066 --> 00:12:44,066
How did you know that?

235
00:12:44,146 --> 00:12:45,426
Miss Sky.

236
00:12:45,426 --> 00:12:51,666
Your strength is that you’re striking, interesting, and memorable.

237
00:12:51,666 --> 00:12:54,986
But your weakness is the face.

238
00:12:54,986 --> 00:12:55,626
The face?

239
00:12:55,626 --> 00:12:58,146
The face.

240
00:12:58,146 --> 00:12:59,506
The face?

241
00:12:59,506 --> 00:13:01,866
Your face.

242
00:13:01,866 --> 00:13:03,866
Oh...my face.

243
00:13:06,266 --> 00:13:10,266
Alright, everyone. The initial evaluation is complete.

244
00:13:10,426 --> 00:13:12,066
Thank you all so much.

245
00:13:12,066 --> 00:13:15,866
Wait, wait, wait! What do you mean "initial evaluation"?

246
00:13:15,866 --> 00:13:19,266
Every time I see you, an evaluation is happening.

247
00:13:19,266 --> 00:13:22,386
Whoever gets the highest score

248
00:13:22,826 --> 00:13:25,986
becomes "The First Class."

249
00:13:25,986 --> 00:13:27,066
Huh?

250
00:13:27,066 --> 00:13:31,066
Does that mean not everyone gets to fly First Class?

251
00:13:32,506 --> 00:13:35,866
Are some of us going back to Economy?

252
00:13:35,866 --> 00:13:39,866
No. Because from now on, there is only First Class.

253
00:13:41,146 --> 00:13:43,226
So that means those who don't make the cut...

254
00:13:43,226 --> 00:13:44,666
Go home.

255
00:13:44,666 --> 00:13:47,586
Say goodbye to Glamorous Airline.

256
00:13:47,586 --> 00:13:48,706
Are we clear?

257
00:13:48,706 --> 00:13:50,906
I’ll see you next Monday in training.

258
00:13:50,906 --> 00:13:55,986
I want you all to embody the soul of First Class.

259
00:13:55,986 --> 00:13:58,786
Focus and bring that spirit out.

260
00:13:58,786 --> 00:14:01,706
Because from now on, every step you take will be scored.

261
00:14:01,706 --> 00:14:05,706
Including your looks.

262
00:14:06,306 --> 00:14:09,586
Looks, looks, looks, looks.

263
00:14:09,586 --> 00:14:10,586
See you then.

264
00:14:14,906 --> 00:14:18,906
Wait, "The Looks"? We need a meeting, guys. Come on!

265
00:14:21,306 --> 00:14:22,746
Let’s cooperate!

266
00:14:22,746 --> 00:14:24,586
I’m heading home. See you later.

267
00:14:24,586 --> 00:14:28,586
Hey, Chai! How can you just leave?
This is a huge deal!

268
00:14:28,826 --> 00:14:31,826
Sky, it’s me, Chai.

269
00:14:32,946 --> 00:14:33,946
And?

270
00:14:33,986 --> 00:14:40,906
Look, there's nothing to worry about.
It's just... you know..."that," right?

271
00:14:40,906 --> 00:14:41,786
Huh?

272
00:14:41,786 --> 00:14:43,146
I’m going home.

273
00:14:43,146 --> 00:14:44,546
What "that"?

274
00:14:44,546 --> 00:14:47,306
What is wrong with him?
Where is he rushing off to?

275
00:14:47,306 --> 00:14:49,826
Gift...oh.

276
00:14:49,826 --> 00:14:50,466
Gift!

277
00:14:50,466 --> 00:14:51,626
She’s gone too.

278
00:14:51,626 --> 00:14:54,586
Ugh, they’re all gone. They’re no help at all.

279
00:14:54,586 --> 00:14:55,546
So now...

280
00:14:55,546 --> 00:14:56,746
It’s just...

281
00:14:56,746 --> 00:14:59,866
you, me, and these...

282
00:14:59,866 --> 00:15:02,986
Mom, Glamorous is changing everything.

283
00:15:02,986 --> 00:15:04,906
I don't even know what to do anymore.

284
00:15:04,906 --> 00:15:08,906
I swear, does his mom have nothing better to do all day?

285
00:15:09,066 --> 00:15:10,226
Kree!

286
00:15:10,226 --> 00:15:11,226
Ms. Petchgam Ploy...

287
00:15:11,226 --> 00:15:11,586
Kree!

288
00:15:11,586 --> 00:15:12,786
Huh?

289
00:15:12,786 --> 00:15:13,946
What is wrong with you?

290
00:15:13,946 --> 00:15:16,186
I’m just...enchanted. It’s nothing.

291
00:15:16,186 --> 00:15:17,466
Just because she knows your name?

292
00:15:17,466 --> 00:15:19,706
She even called me "Mr. Kreetha"!

293
00:15:19,706 --> 00:15:21,346
And what do people usually call me?

294
00:15:21,346 --> 00:15:22,906
Kree, bitch...

295
00:15:22,906 --> 00:15:24,306
Yep. Sounds about right.

296
00:15:24,306 --> 00:15:25,466
Stop daydreaming, Kree.

297
00:15:25,466 --> 00:15:28,226
That Purser basically called our friend "Ugly" to her face!

298
00:15:28,226 --> 00:15:29,866
Don't keep rubbing it in!

299
00:15:29,866 --> 00:15:31,226
I just can't stand it!

300
00:15:31,226 --> 00:15:32,346
Stop it, I’m begging you!

301
00:15:32,346 --> 00:15:36,186
She went like this, "Face, face..."
She meant "Ugly face"!

302
00:15:36,186 --> 00:15:36,826
I’m literally bowing to you now, stop!

303
00:15:36,826 --> 00:15:38,266
You might not feel it, but I’m hurting!

304
00:15:38,266 --> 00:15:39,266
I’m your friend!

305
00:15:40,626 --> 00:15:41,386
Don't repeat it!

306
00:15:41,386 --> 00:15:43,386
Ugly face! And she was pointing right at yours!

307
00:15:51,146 --> 00:15:52,146
It’s a bit too big.

308
00:16:12,946 --> 00:16:16,946
Chai, do you really think the others won’t find out we’re living together?

309
00:16:17,826 --> 00:16:21,026
Nobody would ever guess we’d rent a house together.

310
00:16:21,026 --> 00:16:22,466
We’ve been acting so low-key.

311
00:16:22,466 --> 00:16:23,426
For real.

312
00:16:23,426 --> 00:16:26,986
Pooling our rent makes it so much cheaper.

313
00:16:26,986 --> 00:16:30,986
And we get a bigger space. Mega clever!

314
00:16:31,306 --> 00:16:34,546
But seriously, are we really not going to tell anyone?

315
00:16:34,546 --> 00:16:36,586
Think about it. If the others knew...

316
00:16:36,586 --> 00:16:39,586
do you think we’d have a single moment of peace like this?

317
00:16:39,586 --> 00:16:43,586
That mob would be swarming this place in a heartbeat.

318
00:16:44,546 --> 00:16:47,906
It’s better with just the two of us.

319
00:16:47,906 --> 00:16:48,906
Two of us?

320
00:16:52,026 --> 00:16:55,026
Yeah. Just us, alone.

321
00:16:58,266 --> 00:17:06,186
Shit, I’m living in the same house as Chai, just the two of us.*

322
00:17:06,186 --> 00:17:10,186
This feels like...

323
00:17:11,346 --> 00:17:12,066
Wow!

324
00:17:12,066 --> 00:17:13,626
Whoa!

325
00:17:13,626 --> 00:17:15,826
Nice house!

326
00:17:15,826 --> 00:17:16,626
How the hell did you guys get here?

327
00:17:16,626 --> 00:17:18,386
Well, you guys said you were going home.

328
00:17:18,386 --> 00:17:20,826
So we figured we’d come home too, right?

329
00:17:20,826 --> 00:17:22,186
We?

330
00:17:22,186 --> 00:17:23,106
Yep.

331
00:17:23,106 --> 00:17:29,426
Mom, I’m here! I’ve arrived at Tid-Gift and Chai’s house.

332
00:17:29,426 --> 00:17:33,426
They rented it together to save money,
and it actually looks pretty decent!

333
00:17:35,666 --> 00:17:36,906
How did you find out?

334
00:17:36,906 --> 00:17:38,906
The real question is... who doesn’t know?

335
00:17:39,866 --> 00:17:43,866
This house is amazing.
It even has a swimming pool in the backyard!

336
00:17:44,226 --> 00:17:48,226
It’s perfect. And it’s only 70,000.

337
00:17:49,946 --> 00:17:51,466
But we can't afford that...

338
00:17:51,466 --> 00:17:53,666
The whole point of us renting together was to save money, remember?

339
00:17:53,666 --> 00:17:55,666
What are you guys renting?

340
00:17:58,266 --> 00:17:59,906
Amulets.

341
00:17:59,906 --> 00:18:01,786
You know, Thai amulets.

342
00:18:01,786 --> 00:18:03,826
You? Renting amulets?

343
00:18:03,826 --> 00:18:10,906
It’s a Phra Somdej, Closed-Eye print,
original ancient powder, in a perfect "Sa-mao" radiant arch.

344
00:18:10,906 --> 00:18:14,906
With the "Three-Yant" inscription of Chao Khun Wisut,
Wat Chan Phaya, 1964 edition.

345
00:18:18,426 --> 00:18:22,426
Oh...okay.

346
00:18:31,226 --> 00:18:34,106
Wait, since when do you know anything about amulets?

347
00:18:34,106 --> 00:18:36,106
I watched that Pae Arak's movie about amulets last night.

348
00:18:39,706 --> 00:18:41,026
That was a pretty smooth lie back then.

349
00:18:41,026 --> 00:18:44,386
Wait, what did you call that Phra Somdej again?

350
00:18:44,386 --> 00:18:47,506
It’s a Closed-Eye print, original ancient powder, in perfect condition.

351
00:18:47,506 --> 00:18:49,346
With a "Sa-mao" radiant arch.

352
00:18:49,346 --> 00:18:52,346
It’s pronounced "Se-ma", you hillbilly!

353
00:18:52,346 --> 00:18:55,306
And that specific model of Phra Somdej goes for over half a million.

354
00:18:55,306 --> 00:18:57,026
Not some sixty or seventy thousand baht bargain.

355
00:18:57,026 --> 00:18:57,866
How do you even know that?

356
00:18:57,866 --> 00:19:01,306
How could I not? My dad is literally an amulet grandmaster!

357
00:19:01,306 --> 00:19:03,306
You two are such terrible liars.

358
00:19:24,866 --> 00:19:28,146
Alright, enough! That's it, that's it! Everyone, out!

359
00:19:28,146 --> 00:19:29,986
Go home already! Move!

360
00:19:29,986 --> 00:19:32,506
Go!

361
00:19:32,506 --> 00:19:33,186
Chaba, what are you doing?

362
00:19:33,186 --> 00:19:34,866
I’m not hungry...

363
00:19:34,866 --> 00:19:36,866
Hey, stop it!

364
00:19:36,866 --> 00:19:37,306
Get out! Get out!

365
00:19:37,306 --> 00:19:38,066
Out! Out! Out!

366
00:19:38,066 --> 00:19:38,666
Please, get out.

367
00:19:38,666 --> 00:19:39,666
Wait, wait, wait!

368
00:19:39,666 --> 00:19:42,826
Aren't we supposed to have a meeting about Ms. Petchgam Ploy first?

369
00:19:42,826 --> 00:19:45,706
I already told you, I’m not worried.

370
00:19:45,706 --> 00:19:46,706
Now, go home!

371
00:19:46,706 --> 00:19:49,026
We’re all going to be fine anyway, so don't worry about it.

372
00:19:49,026 --> 00:19:51,266
For real, I’m super chill too.

373
00:19:51,266 --> 00:19:52,266
This way!

374
00:19:54,626 --> 00:19:56,506
I told you, you’ve been working out too much.

375
00:19:56,506 --> 00:19:58,426
She’s got Punpun Sutatta as her idol.

376
00:19:58,426 --> 00:19:58,826
Exactly.

377
00:19:58,826 --> 00:20:00,186
You want to compete in Hyrox like her, don't you?

378
00:20:00,186 --> 00:20:01,186
Yes!

379
00:20:01,546 --> 00:20:02,666
Go, go, go!

380
00:20:02,666 --> 00:20:03,426
What the hell?

381
00:20:03,426 --> 00:20:06,226
We’ll come visit again soon!

382
00:20:06,226 --> 00:20:07,226
Nice house, by the way!

383
00:20:11,786 --> 00:20:12,866
Go, go!

384
00:20:12,866 --> 00:20:14,986
Bye, Mom! See you later, Mom!

385
00:20:14,986 --> 00:20:16,706
Goodbye! Bye! Bye!

386
00:20:16,706 --> 00:20:17,226
Mom!

387
00:20:17,226 --> 00:20:18,226
Move it!

388
00:20:19,426 --> 00:20:21,426
What is wrong with them?

389
00:20:24,306 --> 00:20:25,386
We’re screwed.

390
00:20:25,386 --> 00:20:26,826
What are we going to do now?

391
00:20:26,826 --> 00:20:29,386
I already paid a full year's deposit for this house! What now?

392
00:20:29,386 --> 00:20:31,386
Change the locks. Change the passcode!

393
00:20:35,746 --> 00:20:37,226
Fah, I love you.

394
00:20:37,226 --> 00:20:40,146
Oh! Oh! Stop it, Daddy!

395
00:20:40,146 --> 00:20:44,146
If I’m going to lose my virginity, I better become a flight attendant!

396
00:20:44,386 --> 00:20:47,026
You don't need to lose anything to be a flight attendant, Fah.

397
00:20:47,026 --> 00:20:48,866
Just come to Yeppy Clinic.

398
00:20:48,866 --> 00:20:54,066
Because I, Doctor Yep, will tighten and sculpt your face exactly how you want it.

399
00:20:54,066 --> 00:20:55,506
Come see me.

400
00:20:55,506 --> 00:20:58,466
I know...you all want to get 'Yepped'.

401
00:20:58,466 --> 00:21:02,466
Wow..."Yep" and "Pee"? That’s quite a combo.

402
00:21:03,666 --> 00:21:07,666
Seriously, Chai? Is that all you ever think about?

403
00:21:07,826 --> 00:21:10,186
Doctor Yep is a massive social media sensation!

404
00:21:10,186 --> 00:21:11,906
If he does our faces...

405
00:21:11,906 --> 00:21:14,666
we’re definitely getting promoted to First Class.

406
00:21:14,666 --> 00:21:17,186
The three of us.

407
00:21:17,186 --> 00:21:19,226
Sky! How did you get here?

408
00:21:19,226 --> 00:21:21,706
You two are seriously the worst liars ever.

409
00:21:21,706 --> 00:21:25,026
Sneaking off to get your faces done without me?

410
00:21:25,026 --> 00:21:27,426
What? Trying to gatekeep the glow-up?

411
00:21:27,426 --> 00:21:30,866
It's not like that! It's just that Doctor Yep is so hard to book.

412
00:21:30,866 --> 00:21:34,106
I practically had to beg on my knees just to get these two slots!

413
00:21:34,106 --> 00:21:36,946
Oh, don't say that. I'm willing to do it.

414
00:21:36,946 --> 00:21:39,626
Oh, you want me to dance? I can’t dance right now!

415
00:21:39,626 --> 00:21:41,386
Please send the orange heart for me!

416
00:21:41,386 --> 00:21:43,066
Send me some stickers too!

417
00:21:43,066 --> 00:21:46,786
Oh, shit, shit, shit, shit.

418
00:21:46,786 --> 00:21:49,666
I mean...the poop sticker!
Oh, the new one is so cute.

419
00:21:49,666 --> 00:21:51,666
If anyone has a problem, just comment below.

420
00:21:51,666 --> 00:21:54,026
Doctor Yep answers every single comment.

421
00:21:54,026 --> 00:21:58,026
Because I know...you all want to get 'Yepped' by me.

422
00:21:58,066 --> 00:22:01,066
Alright, I’m ending the live now. Bye-bye!

423
00:22:05,266 --> 00:22:07,986
Excuse me, Doctor? I asked the staff out front...

424
00:22:07,986 --> 00:22:13,266
if I could get a consultation for two cases while you're free?

425
00:22:13,266 --> 00:22:16,746
Actually, four! My friend Chaba is on her way.

426
00:22:16,746 --> 00:22:19,506
No. This is my private time.

427
00:22:19,506 --> 00:22:20,746
Wait...what?

428
00:22:20,746 --> 00:22:23,266
In your live stream, you said you take consultations from every comment!

429
00:22:23,266 --> 00:22:24,906
Then go comment there.

430
00:22:24,906 --> 00:22:27,026
Watch the live stream.

431
00:22:27,026 --> 00:22:29,746
How does he become a completely different person
the second the camera is off?

432
00:22:29,746 --> 00:22:32,786
Doctor, please help us!

433
00:22:32,786 --> 00:22:36,066
If our faces don't improve, we’ll never get to fly.

434
00:22:36,066 --> 00:22:37,626
We'll all end up unemployed!

435
00:22:37,626 --> 00:22:38,786
Are you guys flight attendants?

436
00:22:38,786 --> 00:22:39,866
You can tell just by looking, right?

437
00:22:39,866 --> 00:22:42,906
They actually let faces like these fly?

438
00:22:42,906 --> 00:22:45,746
Right now, we only fly Economy.

439
00:22:45,746 --> 00:22:48,466
But we’re trying to upgrade to First Class.

440
00:22:48,466 --> 00:22:50,426
You...you have the bone structure of a superstar, Davika.

441
00:22:50,426 --> 00:22:52,306
Me?

442
00:22:52,306 --> 00:22:56,026
But your skin texture is a national crisis.

443
00:22:56,026 --> 00:22:59,426
Uh...it's just a few tiny pits, right?

444
00:22:59,426 --> 00:23:03,426
In the medical world, we don't call those "pits."

445
00:23:03,746 --> 00:23:05,586
We call those "canyons."

446
00:23:05,586 --> 00:23:09,066
A pit is like this. A canyon is like this.

447
00:23:09,066 --> 00:23:11,466
And your face...It’s rejecting collagen.

448
00:23:11,466 --> 00:23:12,946
Your skin is literally spitting out your foundation.

449
00:23:12,946 --> 00:23:16,666
And your pores?
They’re in a domestic dispute with your moisturizer.

450
00:23:16,666 --> 00:23:19,506
Is that...medical terminology?

451
00:23:19,506 --> 00:23:21,506
No, that’s just the truth.

452
00:23:22,546 --> 00:23:24,546
That's harsh.

453
00:23:24,986 --> 00:23:27,706
What about the two of us?

454
00:23:27,706 --> 00:23:28,826
Let’s start with you, sweetie.

455
00:23:28,826 --> 00:23:29,546
Yes?

456
00:23:29,546 --> 00:23:31,546
You’re pretty.

457
00:23:31,546 --> 00:23:33,666
Pretty like a "tax deduction."

458
00:23:33,666 --> 00:23:36,426
You’re "Ordinary Person" pretty.

459
00:23:36,426 --> 00:23:38,106
But you’re going to fly First Class!

460
00:23:38,106 --> 00:23:40,026
You need to be "Corporate Entity" pretty!

461
00:23:40,026 --> 00:23:44,826
Value-Added Tax pretty! Over-a-million-baht pretty!
But this...this isn't it.

462
00:23:44,826 --> 00:23:45,786
And me?

463
00:23:45,786 --> 00:23:47,426
You’re "OTP" handsome.

464
00:23:47,986 --> 00:23:48,786
Meaning...

465
00:23:48,786 --> 00:23:52,786
Handsome, but requires multi-factor authentication.

466
00:23:52,986 --> 00:23:54,546
Uh...what about my skin?

467
00:23:54,546 --> 00:23:55,546
Your skin is like a delivery man.

468
00:23:55,546 --> 00:23:56,586
The delivery man gives it to the customer.

469
00:23:56,586 --> 00:23:57,826
And the customer sends it right back.

470
00:23:57,826 --> 00:24:01,826
You’re "Cash on Delivery" handsome,
but the package was rejected at the door.

471
00:24:02,026 --> 00:24:03,466
That’s enough, Doctor!

472
00:24:03,466 --> 00:24:06,106
So...you’re not going to take us as patients?

473
00:24:06,106 --> 00:24:07,586
I’ll take you.

474
00:24:07,586 --> 00:24:10,386
I like it. It’s a challenge.

475
00:24:10,386 --> 00:24:11,386
Oh! For real?

476
00:24:19,546 --> 00:24:22,106
Since when did I become a delivery boy?

477
00:24:22,106 --> 00:24:24,106
Here you go, Chaba. Your new uniform.

478
00:24:28,026 --> 00:24:29,026
Hey, Chaba.

479
00:24:31,666 --> 00:24:33,906
Stop. I’m saving my energy. Don't talk to me.

480
00:24:33,906 --> 00:24:39,786
Well, do you want some coffee?
I can go get some for...

481
00:24:39,786 --> 00:24:43,786
Ugh, for me! Go get it before
I pass out from caffeine withdrawal.

482
00:24:45,826 --> 00:24:48,546
I... I’m shy.

483
00:24:48,546 --> 00:24:49,546
Shy of the coffee?

484
00:24:53,866 --> 00:24:57,866
Oh, I get it. The "Puppy" has a crush on Ms. Petchgam Ploy.

485
00:24:59,546 --> 00:25:00,386
Keep it down!

486
00:25:00,386 --> 00:25:01,026
What?

487
00:25:01,026 --> 00:25:02,946
I have a weakness for women with natural beauty.

488
00:25:02,946 --> 00:25:06,146
You mean "natural" as in using natural-ingredient makeup?

489
00:25:06,146 --> 00:25:10,146
No! She’s beautiful even without any makeup on at all.

490
00:25:12,026 --> 00:25:14,346
What do you think she's doing?
Scrubing off the dead skin?

491
00:25:14,346 --> 00:25:16,986
Her skin is so clear without applying anything.

492
00:25:16,986 --> 00:25:18,306
She’s glowing.

493
00:25:18,306 --> 00:25:21,386
She has an aura.

494
00:25:21,386 --> 00:25:24,106
Wow...she is the definition of "Natural Beauty."

495
00:25:24,106 --> 00:25:27,226
Ugh, then why the hell am I even bothering with makeup?

496
00:25:27,226 --> 00:25:30,186
Wait, Chaba! I’ll get that coffee for you right now!

497
00:25:30,186 --> 00:25:32,506
Sure, sure. I’m literally dying.

498
00:25:32,506 --> 00:25:33,506
Take the uniform, Chaba.

499
00:25:42,266 --> 00:25:46,266
Ms. Petchgam Ploy, excuse me...

500
00:25:49,506 --> 00:25:51,906
Quite an eater. Exactly my type.

501
00:25:51,906 --> 00:25:55,706
Hey! When I eat a lot, you just tell me I'm getting fat!

502
00:25:55,706 --> 00:25:57,146
What "type" are you talking about?

503
00:25:57,146 --> 00:26:01,146
Oh, I meant the coffee pot!
It’s exactly the type I like.

504
00:26:02,946 --> 00:26:06,946
And what about your "type," Mr. Kreetha?
What is she like?

505
00:26:15,866 --> 00:26:17,866
Hello, babe? Did you miss me?

506
00:26:19,546 --> 00:26:22,426
Oh! Kree has a "Sugar Mommy"!

507
00:26:22,426 --> 00:26:22,666
It’s not like that!

508
00:26:22,666 --> 00:26:24,826
I saw it with my own eyes!
I’m definitely gossiping about this.

509
00:26:24,826 --> 00:26:25,626
Chaba, wait! It’s not what you think!

510
00:26:25,626 --> 00:26:27,866
I’m telling Sky first. I'm seeing her today.

511
00:26:30,066 --> 00:26:30,746
I'm out.

512
00:26:30,746 --> 00:26:30,946
Chaba!

513
00:26:30,946 --> 00:26:31,986
So, you like them "spicy," Kreetha?

514
